Preheat the #oven{} to 200°C.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Crumble the @feta cheese{50%g} into small pieces.

Cut the @ciabatta{1} in half.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat.

When hot, add half the garlic and stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Next, turn the heat up to high, add the @chopped cavolo nero{100%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Discard any tough stalks from the cavolo nero.

Add 1 tbsp of @water{1%tbsp per person} per person and steam-fry until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @butter beans{1%400g can}(drained and rinsed) in a #sieve{}, then add them to the pan with the cavolo nero.

Add the @harissa paste{50%g}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, @tomato passata{1%400g jar}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @water{75%ml} for the sauce. Stir to combine.

Bring up to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in another #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} and fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once cooked, transfer the toasted breadcrumbs to a #bowl{} and set aside. Season with @pepper{} and crumble in the feta.

When the bean stew is ready, taste and add more @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine the remaining @garlic clove{1}(grated) and the @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the garlic bread. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Lay the ciabatta onto a #baking tray{}, cut-side up. Spread the garlic mixture on top.

Pop the bread onto the middle shelf of your oven and toast until golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Just before serving, pour the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing and @cider vinegar{15%ml} into a large bowl. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix well to combine. Add the @pea shoots{40%g} to the dressing bowl and toss to coat.

Divide the harissa spiced butter bean stew between your bowls.

Sprinkle the feta crumb on top.

Cut the garlic bread into triangles and serve alongside with the pea shoot salad. Enjoy!